1
00:00:05,881 --> 00:00:08,926
<i>["Headhunt" by Okamoto's]</i>

2
00:00:08,926 --> 00:00:11,970
[man singing in Japanese]

3
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:19,019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

4
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,185
‐ So let's head on in there

5
00:01:00,185 --> 00:01:01,853
and show
those bastards in the Dollars

6
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,356
which one of us
is really insane!

7
00:01:04,356 --> 00:01:06,024
‐ So the thing I'm after here,

8
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:07,651
if you're willing,
is that I'd basically like you

9
00:01:07,651 --> 00:01:09,027
to become the leader
of the Blue Squares.

10
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:11,572
‐ When it moves,
I will follow after.

11
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:13,031
Our target is the girl.

12
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:15,534
The monster may very well
lead us to her.

13
00:01:15,534 --> 00:01:17,160
KINE: Heiwajima was here.

14
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:19,288
Shizuo wasted three of our guys!

15
00:01:24,376 --> 00:01:31,383
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:03,915
MIZUKI: It's disturbing.

17
00:02:03,915 --> 00:02:06,251
‐ [whimpering]
Stop!

18
00:02:06,251 --> 00:02:07,669
You've got it all wrong.

19
00:02:07,669 --> 00:02:09,338
We're not really with
the Dollars, all right?

20
00:02:09,338 --> 00:02:10,964
All we did was sign up online.

21
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:14,217
We have no idea
what the leader looks‐‐

22
00:02:14,217 --> 00:02:17,054
‐ No one gives a rat's ass
about that crap.

23
00:02:17,054 --> 00:02:18,889
Now, bring him in.

24
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:24,186
You email or text him shit.
Just get him here.

25
00:02:25,145 --> 00:02:27,272
MIZUKI: Very disturbing.

26
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:28,273
BAKYURA: Hey, all!

27
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,275
So, quick question.

28
00:02:30,275 --> 00:02:32,903
I'm curious.
Was I really here yesterday?

29
00:02:32,903 --> 00:02:33,945
SAN: Totally!

30
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:34,905
KYO: Well, well, well.

31
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:36,281
If it isn't Bakyura.

32
00:02:36,281 --> 00:02:38,325
How you been?
You have any hard evidence yet

33
00:02:38,325 --> 00:02:40,952
that this girlfriend of yours
is a real live human being

34
00:02:40,952 --> 00:02:43,330
and not a figment
of your imagination?

35
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:44,956
BAKYURA: Nope.
By the way,

36
00:02:44,956 --> 00:02:46,291
did Taro Tanaka show up

37
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,585
in any of the chats yesterday?

38
00:02:48,585 --> 00:02:51,129
MIZUKI: So disturbing.

39
00:02:51,129 --> 00:02:55,300
‐ Hey, nothing to see here.
Get lost.

40
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:57,135
Are those chicks
with the Dollars?

41
00:02:57,135 --> 00:02:59,221
‐ I told you, man.
I don't know!

42
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:00,347
I think
I might've seen his name

43
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:02,474
on the mailing list,
so probably.

44
00:03:02,474 --> 00:03:03,767
‐ Son of a bitch.

45
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,477
Is everyone
and their freaking grandma

46
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:06,728
in the Dollars?

47
00:03:06,728 --> 00:03:08,105
‐ Someone will have called
the cops by now.

48
00:03:08,105 --> 00:03:09,189
Let's roll.
‐ Right.

49
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,524
Huh?

50
00:03:10,524 --> 00:03:13,026
[kids gasping]

51
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:17,072
The guy who started your gang,
he's one serious dirtbag.

52
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:17,989
‐ What?

53
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,616
‐ Those kids are like toddlers.

54
00:03:19,616 --> 00:03:20,784
I'm not fighting them.

55
00:03:20,784 --> 00:03:22,994
MIZUKI: Disturbing.

56
00:03:22,994 --> 00:03:30,043
<i>♪ ♪</i>

57
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:40,053
Everywhere I go, disturbing.

58
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:42,848
More than before.
More than ever.

59
00:03:42,848 --> 00:03:44,349
Yet the same.

60
00:03:44,349 --> 00:03:47,310
Ikebukuro
is one disturbing place.

61
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:50,730
The smell of danger is so thick,
I want to hurl.

62
00:03:52,524 --> 00:03:55,777
‐ What's up?
You guys find Shizuo Heiwajima?

63
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:59,406
‐ Yo, Kazamoto, who the hell
made you the damn boss?

64
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,574
‐ Settle down, dude.

65
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,576
I just asked
a freaking question.

66
00:04:02,576 --> 00:04:05,704
I'm not trying to act like
I'm in charge or anything, bro.

67
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:06,997
‐ You're so full of shit.

68
00:04:06,997 --> 00:04:08,290
[door handle shuffles]
‐ Huh?

69
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:10,333
‐ Put a lid on it, Aozaki.

70
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,002
‐ Hey, boss.

71
00:04:12,002 --> 00:04:13,378
[door closes]

72
00:04:15,088 --> 00:04:18,758
‐ Look, I don't know
who this punk Heiwajima is...

73
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:23,722
But could this guy really
have taken out three of our men

74
00:04:23,722 --> 00:04:25,432
with just his bare hands?

75
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:28,101
‐ Well, he doesn't always use
his bare hands.

76
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:30,812
He's been known to use
an object or two at times.

77
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:31,938
‐ What else do you know?

78
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,231
Have you seen him fight?

79
00:04:33,231 --> 00:04:34,733
‐ Yeah,
I've seen him go at it before,

80
00:04:34,733 --> 00:04:36,526
but it was always
from a distance.

81
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:39,029
It's not like he comes prepared
with tools of his own.

82
00:04:39,029 --> 00:04:41,156
He just grabs
whatever's around at the time.

83
00:04:41,156 --> 00:04:43,241
‐ That's
just typical street fighting.

84
00:04:43,241 --> 00:04:44,576
Any punk who knows his shit

85
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:46,745
has grabbed a rock or 2x4
at some time.

86
00:04:46,745 --> 00:04:49,331
‐ No, no, no, that's not
what I'm talking about.

87
00:04:49,331 --> 00:04:51,875
This guy uses vending machines
and guardrails.

88
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,752
‐ Well,
that's just unimaginative.

89
00:04:53,752 --> 00:04:55,545
Smashing a guy's head
into those things

90
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,713
is kid's stuff.

91
00:04:56,713 --> 00:04:57,923
‐ That's not it, boss.

92
00:04:57,923 --> 00:04:59,299
It's the other way around.

93
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:00,467
‐ What?

94
00:05:00,467 --> 00:05:01,802
‐ He picks up vending machines

95
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,053
and snaps off guardrails

96
00:05:03,053 --> 00:05:04,596
and hurls 'em at people.

97
00:05:04,596 --> 00:05:06,932
‐ Ah, hell! I don't have time
for this bullshit!

98
00:05:06,932 --> 00:05:08,350
‐ He's telling the truth.

99
00:05:08,350 --> 00:05:10,852
Listen, boss.
You're out of the country a lot,

100
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,230
so you don't spend much time
in Ikebukuro,

101
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,649
which is why
you haven't heard of this guy.

102
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:17,108
‐ Mm‐hmm.

103
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:18,610
‐ He hurls all kinds of things,

104
00:05:18,610 --> 00:05:20,946
cars and motorcycles included.

105
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:26,785
‐ Our war with the Asuki group
is gonna come to an end soon.

106
00:05:26,785 --> 00:05:29,454
I don't want word of this
leaking before it does,

107
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:30,622
so do whatever it takes

108
00:05:30,622 --> 00:05:33,041
to smoke out
this Heiwajima punk.

109
00:05:39,798 --> 00:05:42,133
‐ I appreciate your hard work.

110
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:45,011
‐ Well,
we do our best to be thorough.

111
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,305
‐ We owe a big debt
to Mr. Awakusu.

112
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,057
He's always looked out for us.

113
00:05:49,057 --> 00:05:51,977
‐ Lucky for us, there wasn't
much blood this time.

114
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:54,646
If they use one of those
ultraviolet thingamajigs,

115
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:56,982
just tell him
you got a bloody nose, okay?

116
00:05:56,982 --> 00:05:59,276
‐ Heh, that would be nice,
but unfortunately,

117
00:05:59,276 --> 00:06:02,028
the cops would never fall
for a line like that.

118
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:03,947
[all giggling]

119
00:06:05,407 --> 00:06:08,243
Hey, have the guys found
Heiwajima yet?

120
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:10,453
‐ Yeah, well, truth is...

121
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:16,167
‐ You're that Heiwajima guy,
right?

122
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:17,711
‐ [grumbles]

123
00:06:17,711 --> 00:06:20,088
Can I help you?

124
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,506
‐ Listen, punk.
Don't play dumb.

125
00:06:21,506 --> 00:06:23,008
You know what you did.

126
00:06:23,008 --> 00:06:25,302
‐ I didn't kill him,
if that's what you mean.

127
00:06:25,302 --> 00:06:27,470
But you're not gonna believe me,
now, are you?

128
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,223
‐ Well, we ain't the ones
who decide if you did or not.

129
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,182
Get in.

130
00:06:31,182 --> 00:06:32,559
‐ Not happening.

131
00:06:32,559 --> 00:06:34,519
I'm on my way
to beat up the lousy fleabag

132
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,563
who's trying to frame me,
so if you gentlemen

133
00:06:36,563 --> 00:06:38,189
would kindly step aside.

134
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:39,691
‐ Hmm.

135
00:06:39,691 --> 00:06:42,986
<i>♪ ♪</i>

136
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,362
What?

137
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

138
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,491
[men gasping]

139
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:50,368
Ah, come on!
Don't run!

140
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:52,162
Asshole!

141
00:06:52,162 --> 00:06:54,581
‐ He ran away without fighting?

142
00:06:54,581 --> 00:06:56,124
‐ He didn't even take
a swing at them.

143
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:58,126
Maybe he doesn't want
to make enemies of us.

144
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,045
‐ I don't know.
If that's what he's thinking,

145
00:07:00,045 --> 00:07:02,255
why would he kill
any of our guys to begin with?

146
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:05,050
There's no sign that he tried
to touch the vault.

147
00:07:05,050 --> 00:07:07,052
Strong as he is,
he should've been able

148
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,720
to crack that safe like an egg.

149
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,847
We sure
he's the one behind all this?

150
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:12,724
‐ They described the guy
as a blond bartender

151
00:07:12,724 --> 00:07:15,060
with blue shades,
so who else could it be?

152
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:17,604
‐ Well, obviously,
there's no doubt he was here,

153
00:07:17,604 --> 00:07:19,481
but if he did it,
why not kill the guys

154
00:07:19,481 --> 00:07:21,566
who discovered him
instead of running?

155
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:22,734
Doesn't matter.

156
00:07:22,734 --> 00:07:24,402
Either way,
we got to bring him in.

157
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:27,989
If Aozaki or Akabayashi butt in,
things will get complicated.

158
00:07:27,989 --> 00:07:29,157
‐ Mm.
MAN: Sorry, sir.

159
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:30,617
But I've got an urgent message.

160
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:31,576
‐ What is it?

161
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:32,577
‐ We just got a heads‐up

162
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:33,828
from the people out there

163
00:07:33,828 --> 00:07:35,580
searching
for Awakusu's daughter.

164
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:39,167
Guess one of our scouts saw her
yesterday on 60th Floor Street.

165
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:42,212
‐ Kazamoto's the one in charge
of finding Ms. Akane.

166
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:45,215
I don't need to know every
piddly bit of info you get.

167
00:07:45,215 --> 00:07:46,800
‐ Yeah, but the thing is,

168
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,134
when Ms. Akane ran off,

169
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:50,095
she was led out of there
by someone,

170
00:07:50,095 --> 00:07:52,764
and that guy
was Shizuo Heiwajima.

171
00:07:52,764 --> 00:07:54,474
‐ Huh?

172
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:56,101
IZAYA: I got to say,

173
00:07:56,101 --> 00:07:59,646
it's not like you
to go on the run, Shizu‐chan.

174
00:07:59,646 --> 00:08:01,022
And I bet, right about now,

175
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:03,066
the sharper minds
at the Awakusu group

176
00:08:03,066 --> 00:08:06,236
are starting to doubt
you're the real culprit.

177
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:09,155
Does that mean
you're being sensible for once?

178
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:11,408
Or that you've evolved
as a person?

179
00:08:11,408 --> 00:08:13,827
But in your case,
that wouldn't be evolving

180
00:08:13,827 --> 00:08:16,246
as much as it would be
devolving.

181
00:08:16,246 --> 00:08:17,706
Since you're superhuman,

182
00:08:17,706 --> 00:08:20,291
there's not much more evolving
for you to do.

183
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,960
The only thing left for you

184
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:25,130
is to show the world
your immense power.

185
00:08:25,130 --> 00:08:28,550
Now, time for some fun.

186
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:31,469
I do like watching the game
from the sidelines.

187
00:08:31,469 --> 00:08:34,973
It's time you hear the roar
that's beyond the message rooms.

188
00:08:39,310 --> 00:08:40,770
‐ So, then,
what's the word, Mikado?

189
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:42,814
Made up your mind yet?

190
00:08:42,814 --> 00:08:46,026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

191
00:08:46,026 --> 00:08:47,485
SLOAN: Hey, Varona,

192
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:49,404
you think
this is how the hunter feels

193
00:08:49,404 --> 00:08:52,490
who waits forever
for his prey to make a move?

194
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:55,285
VARONA: <i>Da.</i>
<i>Nyet.</i> Hard to tell.

195
00:08:55,285 --> 00:08:58,329
I have never tried
to be hunter of animals before,

196
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,165
but I do know
about hunting humans.

197
00:09:00,165 --> 00:09:02,208
I know this process very well.

198
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,419
You cannot compare it to animal.

199
00:09:04,419 --> 00:09:06,171
<i>‐ Da.</i> Understood.

200
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:07,589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

201
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,549
CELTY: Oh, boy.

202
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:11,468
What should I do?

203
00:09:11,468 --> 00:09:14,179
MIZUKI:
The boy's heart vacillates.

204
00:09:14,179 --> 00:09:16,681
Come the leader
of the Blue Squares.

205
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:19,350
It's as if he's looked
deep into the sinister heart

206
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:21,394
of the younger boy before him,

207
00:09:21,394 --> 00:09:25,023
and he can't bring himself
to accept the reality.

208
00:09:25,023 --> 00:09:26,858
‐ Is the fact that right now,

209
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:28,902
you're smiling.

210
00:09:30,028 --> 00:09:31,696
MIZUKI: The boy stands firm.

211
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:34,449
Never once in his life
has he known rage,

212
00:09:34,449 --> 00:09:36,242
but right now,
a scream is burning

213
00:09:36,242 --> 00:09:38,536
to leap from the pit
of his stomach.

214
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:39,954
MIKADO: What's happening?

215
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:42,540
Why do I feel like
my insides are gonna burst?

216
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:46,544
MIZUKI: What rose up inside
of him wasn't a howl of denial

217
00:09:46,544 --> 00:09:49,047
but an intense wave of nausea.

218
00:09:49,047 --> 00:09:50,632
He suddenly realized

219
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:54,260
that what the boy pointed out
to him was the truth.

220
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:56,304
MIKADO: Huh? What?

221
00:09:56,304 --> 00:09:58,264
MIZUKI:
He doesn't think he was smiling,

222
00:09:58,264 --> 00:09:59,224
but is he right?

223
00:09:59,224 --> 00:10:01,434
MIKADO: Wait. Was I?

224
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:02,644
AOBA: Hello?

225
00:10:02,644 --> 00:10:05,230
Are you all right, there?

226
00:10:05,230 --> 00:10:06,689
‐ Ah!

227
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,191
‐ Whoa. Uncool.

228
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:11,194
My cute face shouldn't have you
freaking out like that.

229
00:10:11,194 --> 00:10:13,238
It's been, like,
ten minutes already.

230
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:15,323
So do you have a decision
for me?

231
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:18,576
‐ Wait, really?

232
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:20,036
<i>♪ ♪</i>

233
00:10:20,036 --> 00:10:21,412
‐ They only started talking

234
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,248
about the Dollars
getting attacked just now.

235
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:26,084
It seems like things
haven't escalated too much.

236
00:10:26,084 --> 00:10:28,002
‐ Would you mind
if I went home for now

237
00:10:28,002 --> 00:10:29,504
and thought about it?

238
00:10:29,504 --> 00:10:32,549
‐ Yeah, I think we're through
with waiting here.

239
00:10:32,549 --> 00:10:35,009
[Mikado laughs nervously]
[door reverberates]

240
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:39,556
‐ But I've got to go!

241
00:10:39,556 --> 00:10:42,517
I'm supposed to meet up
with Anri in a little bit.

242
00:10:43,935 --> 00:10:45,103
‐ That's the first thing

243
00:10:45,103 --> 00:10:46,479
that comes to your mind
right now?

244
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:47,689
You've got it bad.

245
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:50,608
Just how crazy are you
for that chick?

246
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:52,360
MIKADO: Masaomi even told me.

247
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:55,405
"Stay away from anything to do
with the Dollars."

248
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:56,823
‐ Hmm?

249
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:58,783
[doorbell rings]

250
00:10:58,783 --> 00:11:00,785
SHINRA: Hey, there.
That you, Shizuo?

251
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:02,370
Or maybe it's Orihara,

252
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:04,956
who's had every bone in his body
